TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(1,8,1);
$b = random(1,8,1);
$c = random(1,8,1);
##P(x)=(x^2-$a x + $b)(x-2)-$c
$b1=-2-$a;
$c1=2*$a+$b;
$d1=-2*$b-$c;

$p = nicestring([1,$b1,$c1,$d1]);
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Use long division and the Remainder Theorem to evaluate \(P(c)\), where
\[P(x)= $p, \quad c=2.\]
$BR  
The quotient is \{ ans_rule(20) \}
$BR  
The remainder is \{ ans_rule(20) \}
$BR  
\(P(c)\) = \{ ans_rule(20) \}
$BR  
EOT

$ans1 = "x**2-$a*x+$b";
$ans2 = -$c;
$ans3 = -$c;
&ANS(fun_cmp($ans1));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans2));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans3));

